T1kLhN84rtsZ2bH1pbgKPW\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"ls -la && echo \\\"---TASK---\\\" && cat TASK.md && echo \\\"---INPUTS---\\\" && ls -la inputs/ && echo \\\"---OUTPUT---\\\" && ls -la output/ 2>/dev/null\",\"description\":\"List repo and read task\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3302,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":17035,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":3302},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"global\"},\"diagnostics\":null,\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"e02d62b6-0fc3-47da-a384-485e72dab024\",\"uuid\":\"05b5a7c3-a599-4b89-81a4-d1d280b2d40f\",\"request_id\":\"req_011Ccc5XJCVsxNtvYHtBFAeT\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01T1kLhN84rtsZ2bH1pbgKPW\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"total 64\\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501  staff 4096 Jul  1 21:52 .\\ndrwxr-xr-x 5 501  staff 4096 Jul  1 21:50 ..\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._CLAUDE.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._GOAL.txt\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._TASK.md\\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._inputs\\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._output\\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._run.sh\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff  521 Jul  1 21:50 CLAUDE.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff 1189 Jul  1 21:50 GOAL.txt\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff 2191 Jul  1 21:50 TASK.md\\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501  staff 4096 Jul  1 21:50 inputs\\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501  staff 4096 Jul  1 21:51 output\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  4622 Jul  1 21:52 run.log\\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 501  staff  318 Jul  1 21:50 run.sh\\n---TASK---\\n# TASK — Calculation note: passive reactor cavity cooling\\n\\nYou are an engineer. Produce a **calculation note** for a passive **Reactor Cavity Cooling\\nSystem (RCCS)** — the system that removes a high-temperature reactor's decay heat after shutdown\\nwith **no pumps**: a hot vessel wall transfers heat across an air-filled cavity to a bank of\\nsteel riser ducts, and the air in those ducts warms, rises by buoyancy, and carries the heat up\\na chimney by natural circulation.\\n\\nEverything you need is in **`inputs/`** — facility geometry, materials, operating conditions, and\\nwhere each quantity is measured.\\n\\n## What we want\\n\\nFor the operating cases in `inputs/04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md`, predict and report\\n— with your reasoning and assumptions:\\n\\n- the natural-circulation air **mass flow rate**;\\n- the air **temperature rise** across the riser ducts;\\n- the **riser duct wall temperature** and the **heated-wall (mock-vessel) temperature**;\\n- how the removed heat splits between **radiation and convection**;\\n- for the accident (decay-heat) case: the **peak temperatures**, and whether the vessel **stays\\n  below a safe limit** (does the temperature level off, or run away?);\\n- how performance changes with the **outdoor ambient conditions** (air temperature, wind).\\n\\nState your confidence in each number and which assumption is the most uncertain.\\n\\nAt least one key result (the mass flow rate or the heated-wall temperature) must be **cross-checked\\nby an independent, higher-fidelity simulation** (e.g. a CFD calculation with radiation) that you set\\nup and run on this machine, and the two methods reconciled. Prefer prebuilt binaries or Docker for\\nany CFD package; never compile a large code from source.\\n\\n## How to work\\n\\n- You choose the methods and tools. Build from physics and the given conditions.\\n- Put the calculation note and all working files (scripts, models, intermediate results) in\\n  **`output/`**.\\n\\n## Rules\\n\\n- Do **not** look up this facility's published test reports or any pre-made model of it. (They\\n  exist online, and in `refs/` and `sources/` — all off-limits.) Predict the numbers yourself.\\n- Cite the source of any empirical correlation you use.\\n---INPUTS---\\ntotal 52\\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501 staff 4096 Jul  1 21:50 .\\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501 staff 4096 Jul  1 21:52 ..\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._01_facility_geometry.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._02_materials_and_properties.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._03_instrumentation_map.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._README.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 6413 Jul  1 21:50 01_facility_geometry.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 1875 Jul  1 21:50 02_materials_and_properties.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 3996 Jul  1 21:50 03_instrumentation_map.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 2860 Jul  1 21:50 04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  794 Jul  1 21:50 README.md\\n---OUTPUT---\\ntotal 12\\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501 staff 4096 Jul  1 21:51 .\\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501 staff 4096 Jul  1 21:52 ..\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._.gitkeep\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff    0 Jul  1 21:50 .gitkeep\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"e02d62b6-0fc3-47da-a384-485e72dab024\",\"uuid\":\"1252534d-1337-4fb7-aeac-cee2a093fd1b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T21:52:12.090Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"total 64\\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501  staff 4096 Jul  1 21:52 .\\ndrwxr-xr-x 5 501  staff 4096 Jul  1 21:50 ..\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._CLAUDE.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._GOAL.txt\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._TASK.md\\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._inputs\\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._output\\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 501  staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._run.sh\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff  521 Jul  1 21:50 CLAUDE.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff 1189 Jul  1 21:50 GOAL.txt\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501  staff 2191 Jul  1 21:50 TASK.md\\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501  staff 4096 Jul  1 21:50 inputs\\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501  staff 4096 Jul  1 21:51 output\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  4622 Jul  1 21:52 run.log\\n-rwxr-xr-x 1 501  staff  318 Jul  1 21:50 run.sh\\n---TASK---\\n# TASK — Calculation note: passive reactor cavity cooling\\n\\nYou are an engineer. Produce a **calculation note** for a passive **Reactor Cavity Cooling\\nSystem (RCCS)** — the system that removes a high-temperature reactor's decay heat after shutdown\\nwith **no pumps**: a hot vessel wall transfers heat across an air-filled cavity to a bank of\\nsteel riser ducts, and the air in those ducts warms, rises by buoyancy, and carries the heat up\\na chimney by natural circulation.\\n\\nEverything you need is in **`inputs/`** — facility geometry, materials, operating conditions, and\\nwhere each quantity is measured.\\n\\n## What we want\\n\\nFor the operating cases in `inputs/04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md`, predict and report\\n— with your reasoning and assumptions:\\n\\n- the natural-circulation air **mass flow rate**;\\n- the air **temperature rise** across the riser ducts;\\n- the **riser duct wall temperature** and the **heated-wall (mock-vessel) temperature**;\\n- how the removed heat splits between **radiation and convection**;\\n- for the accident (decay-heat) case: the **peak temperatures**, and whether the vessel **stays\\n  below a safe limit** (does the temperature level off, or run away?);\\n- how performance changes with the **outdoor ambient conditions** (air temperature, wind).\\n\\nState your confidence in each number and which assumption is the most uncertain.\\n\\nAt least one key result (the mass flow rate or the heated-wall temperature) must be **cross-checked\\nby an independent, higher-fidelity simulation** (e.g. a CFD calculation with radiation) that you set\\nup and run on this machine, and the two methods reconciled. Prefer prebuilt binaries or Docker for\\nany CFD package; never compile a large code from source.\\n\\n## How to work\\n\\n- You choose the methods and tools. Build from physics and the given conditions.\\n- Put the calculation note and all working files (scripts, models, intermediate results) in\\n  **`output/`**.\\n\\n## Rules\\n\\n- Do **not** look up this facility's published test reports or any pre-made model of it. (They\\n  exist online, and in `refs/` and `sources/` — all off-limits.) Predict the numbers yourself.\\n- Cite the source of any empirical correlation you use.\\n---INPUTS---\\ntotal 52\\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501 staff 4096 Jul  1 21:50 .\\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501 staff 4096 Jul  1 21:52 ..\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._01_facility_geometry.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._02_materials_and_properties.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._03_instrumentation_map.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._README.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 6413 Jul  1 21:50 01_facility_geometry.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 1875 Jul  1 21:50 02_materials_and_properties.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 3996 Jul  1 21:50 03_instrumentation_map.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 2860 Jul  1 21:50 04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  794 Jul  1 21:50 README.md\\n---OUTPUT---\\ntotal 12\\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501 staff 4096 Jul  1 21:51 .\\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501 staff 4096 Jul  1 21:52 ..\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  1 21:50 ._.gitkeep\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff    0 Jul  1 21:50 .gitkeep\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":false}}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"id\":\"msg_01QNVKcxxjMFi1mTFk8uCkYZ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2934,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2131,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":20337,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemer