{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_012KKmCTVzsRafwUVwgCfdNx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All deliverables are in place. The provenance statement is present (line 11–13; the earlier grep just hit a line-wrap). \n\n## Done — goal met\n\n`output/calculation_note.md` exists and reports all seven required results, each with assumptions and a confidence level, plus the provenance statement. Every number was derived from the `inputs/` and first-principles physics — no facility test data consulted.\n\n**Headline predictions (Case 1 baseline, 56 kW scaled duty):**\n\n| # | Result | Value | Confidence |\n|---|--------|-------|-----------|\n| 1 | Natural-circulation mass flow | **0.58 kg/s (35 kg/min)** | Medium (±25%) |\n| 2 | Riser air temperature rise | **≈96 K** (outlet 116 °C) | Medium |\n| 3 | Riser wall / heated-wall (vessel) T | **163 °C front / 390 °C plate** | Med / **Med-high (CFD-confirmed)** |\n| 4 | Radiation : convection split | **93 % : 7 %** (CFD 96:4) | High (>90% radiative) |\n| 5 | Accident peak & stability | **peak ≈390 °C at 84.85 h, levels off — no runaway**, below ~550 °C limit | High (qualitative) |\n| 6 | Weather sensitivity | colder outdoor → more draft/flow, cooler plate (382→401 °C over −18→+24 °C); wind ±15–20% on flow | Med / low-med |\n| 7 | **CFD cross-check** | buoyantSimpleFoam + viewFactor radiation: plate flux 6215 vs 6335 W/m² (**2%**), plate T reconciled to ~2 °C | — |\n\n**Physics story:** riser friction (80% of loop loss) throttles the passive flow, forcing a large ΔT; radiation across the transparent gap carries >90% of the heat, and its T⁴ dependence makes the vessel temperature strongly self-limiting — doubling the load (56→110 kW) raises the plate only to ~528 °C.\n\n**Most uncertain assumption (flagged):** the electric-to-air fraction (~68%, ~32% parasitic loss). Sensitivity band Q = 48–72 kW → plate 364–437 °C; all conclusions hold across it.\n\n**Files in `output/`:** `calculation_note.md`, `airprops.py` (validated air properties), `rccs_model.py` (coupled loop + HT network), `cases.py`, `make_cfd_case.py` + `cfd/` (OpenFOAM case, logs, `RESULTS.md`), `results/results.json`. The independent CFD ran to completion in the Docker OpenFOAM image with surface-to-surface (viewFactor) radiation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":332,"cache_read_input_tokens":187092,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":332},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e02d62b6-0fc3-47da-a384-485e72dab024","uuid":"8de7870f-b60f-4db4-ba76-16131332bfde","request_id":"req_011Ccc7aa5nxsFKi895gpmwi"}
